Units

Each time value is represented as a number of nanoseconds which can be converted to/from a number of units. The number of nanoseconds per unit is defined by subclasses by overriding nanosecondsPerUnit(), and units can be retrieved by subclasses with asUnits(). For example, asUnits() will return the number of hours, based on the number of nanoseconds.

  • asUnits()
  • nanosecondsPerUnit()
  • nanosecondsToUnits(Nanoseconds)
  • unitsToNanoseconds(double)

Conversion

A length of time can be converted to specific time units by calling one of the following methods:

  • TimeMeasurement.asDays()
  • TimeMeasurement.asHours()
  • PointInTime.asJavaInstant()
  • TimeMeasurement.asMicroseconds()
  • TimeMeasurement.asMilliseconds()
  • TimeMeasurement.asMinutes()
